OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1784002678
OL,3,CHeatwave and World Cup shape spending
OL,4,Cfigures for June
OL,6,FIn-store non-food sales were 1.1% down
OL,7,Fyear on year ` below the 12-month
OL,8,Faverage growth of 0.1% ` showing just
OL,9,Fhow much bricks and mortar retailers
OL,10,Fsuffered the effects of the heatwave.
OL,12,FBRC chief executive Helen Dickinson
OL,13,Fsaid: "Retail sales maintained
OL,14,Fmomentum despite June's heatwave.
OL,26,@uD@GOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30503
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1784002678
OL,3,CHeatwave and World Cup shape spending
OL,4,Cfigures for June
OL,6,F"While in-store sales were stifled by
OL,7,Fsoaring temperatures, the proportion
OL,8,Fof sales online was the highest of
OL,9,F2026, bolstered by well-timed
OL,10,Fpromotions. Electric fans and paddling
OL,11,Fpools performed well, as people looked
OL,12,Fto cool off, while the lure of the
OL,13,Fsunshine meant that gaming and big
OL,14,Fticket sales struggled."
OL,16,FLinda Ellett, UK head of consumer,
OL,17,Fretail and leisure markets at KPMG,
OL,18,Fsaid: "Record-breaking temperatures
OL,19,Fcontinued from May into June, with
OL,20,Fretail sales again rising.
OL,26,@nD@AOUvD@XO]zD@GOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
