CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1784002678
OL,3,CHeatwave and World Cup shape spending
OL,4,Cfigures for June
OL,6,F"Demand for fans and air con units
OL,7,Fhelped drive up home appliance sales,
OL,8,Fwith some retailers struggling to
OL,9,Frestock fast enough, while the men's
OL,10,Ffootball World Cup also brought a
OL,11,Fboost for home electrical sales and
OL,12,Ffood and drink."
OL,14,FSeparate figures from Barclays show
OL,15,Fconsumer card spending grew 1.9% year
OL,16,Fon year in June, with a 1.7% increase
OL,17,Fin non-essential spending driven by a
OL,18,Fcombination of stabilising consumer
OL,19,Fconfidence, warm weather and the
OL,20,Farrival of the World Cup.
OL,26,@nD@AOUtD@PO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/7
