OL,3,CHeatwave and World Cup shape spending
OL,4,Cfigures for June
OL,6,FMerchant data from Barclays shows pubs
OL,7,Fenjoyed substantial boosts on England
OL,8,Fmatch days, helped by extended opening
OL,9,Fhours.
OL,11,FPub transactions hit a 2026-peak on
OL,12,FSaturday June 27, when England faced
OL,13,FPanama, at five times the year's daily
OL,14,Faverage ` up 389.9% ` representing a
OL,15,F161.7% year-on-year increase.
OL,17,FCombined figures for Sunday July 5 and
OL,18,FMonday July 6, when the England-Mexico
OL,19,Fkick-off was delayed until 2am BST due
OL,20,Fto the weather, payments tripled, up
OL,21,F201.5% year on year.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30506
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1784002678
OL,3,CHeatwave and World Cup shape spending
OL,4,Cfigures for June
OL,6,FSimilarly, England's draw against
OL,7,FGhana resulted in an unusually busy
OL,8,FTuesday ` on this occasion, June 23 `
OL,9,Ffor the sector, with payments
OL,10,Fprocessed up 244.3% year on year.
OL,12,FJack Meaning, chief UK economist at
OL,13,FBarclays, said: "While additional
OL,14,Fspending around the World Cup will be
OL,15,Fa welcome cushion for the hospitality
OL,16,Fsector, it remains true that the
OL,17,Feconomy has slowed into the middle of
OL,18,Fthe year.
OL,26,@uD@QOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/7
